   ## Root Cause Explanation
   
   The defect is on line 23. The code attempts to dereference `adam1.b2->data`
   four times, but `bob2.data` was intentionally set to `nullptr` on line 20.
   This means `adam1.b2->data` evaluates to `nullptr`, and attempting to
   dereference a null pointer (`*nullptr`) causes undefined behavior and
   triggers a SIGSEGV.
   
